# Manual HTTP probes for the chat module (Phase 5).
#
# How to use:
#   1. Start the server with `task run`.
#   2. Open this file in JetBrains GoLand/IntelliJ or VSCode with the
#      REST Client extension installed.
#   3. Click the gutter icon next to a request to send it.
#
# NOTE — server-sent events:
# The /chat endpoint streams text/event-stream. JetBrains' REST Client
# renders each `event:` / `data:` frame as it arrives. From a terminal
# the equivalent probe is:
#
#   curl -N -X POST http://localhost:3000/chat \
#     -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
#     -d '{"messages":[{"role":"user","content":"hello world go"}]}'
#
# With OPENAI_API_KEY unset the in-memory gateway splits the LAST
# message's content on whitespace and emits one delta per token. With
# the key set, real LLM tokens stream from OpenAI.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### POST {{baseUrl}}/chat — stream a chat completion
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    {"role": "user", "content": "hello world go"}
  ]
}

### POST {{baseUrl}}/chat — multi-turn history (in-memory gateway uses only the LAST user message)
POST {{baseUrl}}/chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "messages": [
    {"role": "system", "content": "you are concise"},
    {"role": "user", "content": "ignored by in-memory gateway"},
    {"role": "assistant", "content": "also ignored"},
    {"role": "user", "content": "echo me"}
  ]
}
